"{\"uid\": \"salon.com-2024-08-03-olympics-black-hair\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Simone Bilesis an Olympic powerhouse.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 37, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Simone Bilesis\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 14}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympic powerhouse\", \"from\": 15, \"to\": 36}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hercomebackat the 2024 ParisOlympicshas kept eyes glued to screens as she racks up gold medal after gold medal.\", \"from\": 38, \"to\": 149, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 2024 ParisOlympicshas\", \"from\": 52, \"to\": 77}, {\"ngram\": \"eyes\", \"from\": 83, \"to\": 87}, {\"ngram\": \"screens\", \"from\": 97, \"to\": 104}, {\"ngram\": \"gold medal\", \"from\": 121, \"to\": 131}, {\"ngram\": \"gold medal\", \"from\": 138, \"to\": 148}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Biles\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 dominance hasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t stopped critics from telling her to \\\"gel up\\\" and \\\"pin up\\\" her hair, or commenting, \\\"Her messy hair is a choice.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d The Olympian took to Instagram to\\u00c2respond, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cGonna hold your hand when I say this, next time you want to comment on a Black girl's hair, JUST DON'T.\\\"\", \"from\": 151, \"to\": 448, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 302, \"end\": 310, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5416798844473305e-14, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Biles\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 dominance\", \"from\": 155, \"to\": 173}, {\"ngram\": \"hasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t\", \"from\": 174, \"to\": 182}, {\"ngram\": \"critics\", \"from\": 191, \"to\": 198}, {\"ngram\": \"her hair\", \"from\": 241, \"to\": 249}, {\"ngram\": \"Her messy hair\", \"from\": 267, \"to\": 281}, {\"ngram\": \"Instagram\", \"from\": 319, \"to\": 328}, {\"ngram\": \"to\\u00c2respond\", \"from\": 329, \"to\": 339}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cGonna\", \"from\": 341, \"to\": 349}, {\"ngram\": \"your hand\", \"from\": 355, \"to\": 364}, {\"ngram\": \"a Black girl's hair\", \"from\": 415, \"to\": 434}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This isn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t the first time Biles has received disparaging comments about her hair; it certainly won\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t be the last.\", \"from\": 450, \"to\": 567, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Biles\", \"from\": 478, \"to\": 483}, {\"ngram\": \"disparaging comments\", \"from\": 497, \"to\": 517}, {\"ngram\": \"her hair\", \"from\": 524, \"to\": 532}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This criticism is not a new experience for Black women but with the spotlight on them in high-profile sports, these athletes are drawing more attention \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 and inevitably, more people with opinions about their appearance.\", \"from\": 568, \"to\": 789, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This criticism\", \"from\": 568, \"to\": 582}, {\"ngram\": \"a new experience\", \"from\": 590, \"to\": 606}, {\"ngram\": \"Black women\", \"from\": 611, \"to\": 622}, {\"ngram\": \"the spotlight\", \"from\": 632, \"to\": 645}, {\"ngram\": \"high-profile sports\", \"from\": 657, \"to\": 676}, {\"ngram\": \"these athletes\", \"from\": 678, \"to\": 692}, {\"ngram\": \"more attention\", \"from\": 705, \"to\": 719}, {\"ngram\": \"inevitably, more people\", \"from\": 728, \"to\": 751}, {\"ngram\": \"opinions\", \"from\": 757, \"to\": 765}, {\"ngram\": \"their appearance\", \"from\": 772, \"to\": 788}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From Biles and\\u00c2Gabby Douglas\\u00c2 to\\u00c2 Dominique Dawes and\\u00c2Sha\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099Carri Richardson, and many others, Black female Olympians are still pressured to explain themselves to hair critics despite the evolving education around Black hair.\", \"from\": 791, \"to\": 1016, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 825, \"end\": 840, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dominique_Dawes\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dominique Dawes\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dominique_Dawes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dominique_Dawes\"}, {\"begin\": 857, \"end\": 867, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1123158231383737e-22, \"text\": \"Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Biles\", \"from\": 796, \"to\": 801}, {\"ngram\": \"many others\", \"from\": 873, \"to\": 884}, {\"ngram\": \"Black female Olympians\", \"from\": 886, \"to\": 908}, {\"ngram\": \"hair critics\", \"from\": 954, \"to\": 966}, {\"ngram\": \"the evolving education\", \"from\": 975, \"to\": 997}, {\"ngram\": \"Black hair\", \"from\": 1005, \"to\": 1015}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Related Before there were superstar Gen Z athletes like Biles, Douglas and Richardson, there was Dawes.\", \"from\": 1018, \"to\": 1122, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1055, \"end\": 1060, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Generation_Z\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gen Z\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Generation_Z\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Generation_Z\"}, {\"begin\": 1082, \"end\": 1089, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_O._Douglas\", \"score\": 0.9999999226993198, \"rank\": 7.730064448216872e-08, \"text\": \"Douglas\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_O._Douglas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_O._Douglas\"}, {\"begin\": 1094, \"end\": 1104, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1123158231383737e-22, \"text\": \"Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Biles\", \"from\": 1074, \"to\": 1079}, {\"ngram\": \"Dawes\", \"from\": 1115, \"to\": 1120}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1996, Dawes became the first Black person to win an individual Olympic medal in gymnastics.\", \"from\": 1123, \"to\": 1217, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Dawes\", \"from\": 1132, \"to\": 1137}, {\"ngram\": \"the first Black person\", \"from\": 1145, \"to\": 1167}, {\"ngram\": \"an individual Olympic medal\", \"from\": 1175, \"to\": 1202}, {\"ngram\": \"gymnastics\", \"from\": 1206, \"to\": 1216}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, while in\\u00c2 Atlanta, the 19-year-old was criticized for her hair being \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009caskew.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d She wore her pressed-out or relaxed hair in a slicked-back bun with a gold scrunchie.\", \"from\": 1218, \"to\": 1394, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1237, \"end\": 1244, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.3964323815493674e-22, \"text\": \"Atlanta\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her hair\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 1289}, {\"ngram\": \"her pressed-out or relaxed hair\", \"from\": 1318, \"to\": 1349}, {\"ngram\": \"a slicked-back bun\", \"from\": 1353, \"to\": 1371}, {\"ngram\": \"a gold scrunchie\", \"from\": 1377, \"to\": 1393}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She also had wispy bangs to match.\\u00c2 Shesaidof the experience in 2012, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cAs gymnasts, we are not concerned about our hair.\", \"from\": 1395, \"to\": 1518, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"wispy bangs\", \"from\": 1408, \"to\": 1419}, {\"ngram\": \"the experience\", \"from\": 1441, \"to\": 1455}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cAs gymnasts\", \"from\": 1465, \"to\": 1479}, {\"ngram\": \"our hair\", \"from\": 1508, \"to\": 1516}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If you look back at videos of myself at the Olympics, you\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll see I wasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t so concerned with how I looked and if I was, I may have never made it to the Olympic games.\", \"from\": 1519, \"to\": 1688, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"videos\", \"from\": 1539, \"to\": 1545}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1559, \"to\": 1571}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic games\", \"from\": 1670, \"to\": 1687}]}, {\"sentence\": \"My focus wasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t on appearance, it was on achievement.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d This isn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t the first time Biles has received disparaging comments about her hair; it certainly won\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t be the last.\", \"from\": 1689, \"to\": 1866, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"My focus\", \"from\": 1689, \"to\": 1697}, {\"ngram\": \"appearance\", \"from\": 1710, \"to\": 1720}, {\"ngram\": \"achievement.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d\", \"from\": 1732, \"to\": 1747}, {\"ngram\": \"Biles\", \"from\": 1776, \"to\": 1781}, {\"ngram\": \"disparaging comments\", \"from\": 1795, \"to\": 1815}, {\"ngram\": \"her hair\", \"from\": 1822, \"to\": 1830}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Similarly, nearly 20 years after Dawes\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 gold win, 16-year-old Douglas entranced the country with her gymnastics at the 2012 London Olympics.\", \"from\": 1868, \"to\": 2010, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1932, \"end\": 1939, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_O._Douglas\", \"score\": 0.9999999226993198, \"rank\": 7.730064448216872e-08, \"text\": \"Douglas\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_O._Douglas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_O._Douglas\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Dawes\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 gold win\", \"from\": 1901, \"to\": 1918}, {\"ngram\": \"the country\", \"from\": 1950, \"to\": 1961}, {\"ngram\": \"her gymnastics\", \"from\": 1967, \"to\": 1981}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2012 London Olympics\", \"from\": 1985, \"to\": 2009}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She wore\\u00c2 her hair straightened in a slicked-back ponytail, but even this style was targeted by\\u00c2 both white and Black critics who called into question the edges of her hairline.\", \"from\": 2011, \"to\": 2188, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"wore\\u00c2\", \"from\": 2015, \"to\": 2020}, {\"ngram\": \"her hair\", \"from\": 2021, \"to\": 2029}, {\"ngram\": \"a slicked-back ponytail\", \"from\": 2046, \"to\": 2069}, {\"ngram\": \"even this style\", \"from\": 2075, \"to\": 2090}, {\"ngram\": \"both white and Black critics\", \"from\": 2108, \"to\": 2136}, {\"ngram\": \"question\", \"from\": 2153, \"to\": 2161}, {\"ngram\": \"the edges\", \"from\": 2162, \"to\": 2171}, {\"ngram\": \"her hairline\", \"from\": 2175, \"to\": 2187}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the Black community, if edges are not slicked back with gel or edge control, the appearance can be deemed as \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cunkept\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d and \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cembarrassing.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d\\u00c2 During the Rio Games in 2016, Douglassaid, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cDid I choose my hair texture?\", \"from\": 2189, \"to\": 2415, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Black community\", \"from\": 2192, \"to\": 2211}, {\"ngram\": \"edges\", \"from\": 2216, \"to\": 2221}, {\"ngram\": \"gel\", \"from\": 2248, \"to\": 2251}, {\"ngram\": \"edge control\", \"from\": 2255, \"to\": 2267}, {\"ngram\": \"the appearance\", \"from\": 2269, \"to\": 2283}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cembarrassing.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d\\u00c2\", \"from\": 2318, \"to\": 2338}, {\"ngram\": \"the Rio Games\", \"from\": 2346, \"to\": 2359}, {\"ngram\": \"Douglassaid\", \"from\": 2369, \"to\": 2380}, {\"ngram\": \"my hair texture\", \"from\": 2398, \"to\": 2413}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No.\", \"from\": 2416, \"to\": 2419, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m grateful for having this hair on my head.\", \"from\": 2420, \"to\": 2467, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099m\", \"from\": 2420, \"to\": 2425}, {\"ngram\": \"this hair\", \"from\": 2446, \"to\": 2455}, {\"ngram\": \"my head\", \"from\": 2459, \"to\": 2466}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When you read that hurtful stuff you\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re like \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0098OK, wow.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d In an article fromthe Daily Beast, a Black woman interviewed by the publication said, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI just hate the way [Douglas\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099] hair looks with all those pins and gel.\", \"from\": 2468, \"to\": 2695, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2571, \"end\": 2576, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_people\", \"score\": 0.9999999985711838, \"rank\": 1.1053339515076857e-09, \"text\": \"Black\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_people\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that hurtful stuff\", \"from\": 2482, \"to\": 2500}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0098OK\", \"from\": 2515, \"to\": 2520}, {\"ngram\": \"an article\", \"from\": 2536, \"to\": 2546}, {\"ngram\": \"fromthe Daily Beast\", \"from\": 2547, \"to\": 2566}, {\"ngram\": \"the publication\", \"from\": 2597, \"to\": 2612}, {\"ngram\": \"the way\", \"from\": 2634, \"to\": 2641}, {\"ngram\": \"hair\", \"from\": 2655, \"to\": 2659}, {\"ngram\": \"all those pins\", \"from\": 2671, \"to\": 2685}, {\"ngram\": \"gel\", \"from\": 2690, \"to\": 2693}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I wish someone could have helped her make it look better since she\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s being seen all over the world.\", \"from\": 2696, \"to\": 2797, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"someone\", \"from\": 2703, \"to\": 2710}, {\"ngram\": \"she\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s\", \"from\": 2759, \"to\": 2766}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 2787, \"to\": 2796}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She representing for Black women everywhere.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s taboo culturally to be seen in public with a kinky hairline and your ponytail is straight,\\\" celebrity hairstylist Larry Simms for Mary J. Blige and Gabrielle Union told The Daily Beast.\", \"from\": 2798, \"to\": 3042, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2971, \"end\": 2982, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Simms\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Larry Simms\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Simms\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Simms\"}, {\"begin\": 2987, \"end\": 2991, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_Shelley\", \"score\": 0.999999999915417, \"rank\": 7.501370559075127e-11, \"text\": \"Mary\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_Shelley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_Shelley\"}, {\"begin\": 3015, \"end\": 3020, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3147593266754952e-19, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Black women everywhere.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s taboo\", \"from\": 2819, \"to\": 2861}, {\"ngram\": \"public\", \"from\": 2887, \"to\": 2893}, {\"ngram\": \"a kinky hairline\", \"from\": 2899, \"to\": 2915}, {\"ngram\": \"your ponytail\", \"from\": 2920, \"to\": 2933}, {\"ngram\": \"The Daily Beast\", \"from\": 3025, \"to\": 3040}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThe textures don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t match her own hair and the added-on hair, and that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a problem.\", \"from\": 3043, \"to\": 3132, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThe textures\", \"from\": 3043, \"to\": 3058}, {\"ngram\": \"her own hair\", \"from\": 3073, \"to\": 3085}, {\"ngram\": \"the added-on hair\", \"from\": 3090, \"to\": 3107}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I think Black girls in particular view her as a representation of themselves for the world to see.\", \"from\": 3133, \"to\": 3231, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Black girls\", \"from\": 3141, \"to\": 3152}, {\"ngram\": \"a representation\", \"from\": 3179, \"to\": 3195}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 3214, \"to\": 3223}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She just needs some Smooth and Shine gel and she\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099d be OK.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 Daily Beast's reporter Allison Samuels explained, \\\"The texture of black and African-American hair varies, and extreme heat and sweat can cause the strands to revert to their natural state.\", \"from\": 3232, \"to\": 3487, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3269, \"end\": 3272, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hair_gel\", \"score\": 0.9999999982856025, \"rank\": 1.7145844270646472e-09, \"text\": \"gel\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hair_gel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hair_gel\"}, {\"begin\": 3305, \"end\": 3310, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beauty_and_the_Beast\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.267712526312583e-18, \"text\": \"Beast\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beauty_and_the_Beast\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beauty_and_the_Beast\"}, {\"begin\": 3322, \"end\": 3329, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allison_Engine_Company\", \"score\": 0.9999989931835055, \"rank\": 1.0066599422739508e-06, \"text\": \"Allison\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allison_Engine_Company\"